---
description: Apply strict TypeScript standards for backend and frontend code (NestJS, Next.js)
globs: volley-app-backend/**/*.ts, volley-app-frontend/**/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: false
---
Strict Types:
- Enable strict compiler options
- No `any` or `unknown`
- No non-null assertions `!`
- Prefer type guards, not casts
- Prefer generics over `as`

Interfaces and Types:
- Use `interface` for extensible objects
- Use `type` for unions and primitives

Nullability:
- Avoid nullable returns; use Result types

Enumerations:
- Prefer string literal unions to enums
- Use const enums if needed
- Define enum values explicitly

Lint & Error:
- Catch errors as `unknown`; narrow safely

Generics:
- Use descriptive type parameter names

Prohibitions:
- No `eslint-disable` comments
- No `@ts-ignore` or `@ts-expect-error`
- No implicit any; no loose casts

Quality Gates:
- Lint with zero warnings
- Type-check with `--noEmit`
